===Etymology===
The name was first attested in 1194 as {{der|en|non|Svalbarð}}, from {{m|non|svalr||cold}} + {{m|non|barð||edge, ridge, turf, beard}}, thus roughly meaning “cold shore,” probably alluding to the treeless landscape mostly covered with grass, although there is uncertainty as to what the name originally referred to.

